mpl` can be exercised with Scala 3 inline macros and `-Yretain-trees`, but JaCoCo/dynamic-access coverage is collected during JVM test execution, not during test-source macro expansion.\\n- The public `find*ValueEntriesImpl` paths do not call `ValueEnumMacros$ValueOfFromExpr.unapply` at test runtime.\\n- Reaching `unapply` directly would require internal/private implementation access, direct reflection, mocked `Quotes`/`Expr`, or runtime Scala compiler/staging behavior. Those are outside the allowed supported public API path and would conflict with the Native Image execution constraints.\\n\\nCurrent focused test coverage remains in:\\n- `tests/src/com.beachape/enumeratum-macros_3/1.9.0/src/test/scala/com_beachape/enumeratum_macros_3/ValueEnumMacrosInnerValueOfFromExprTest.scala`\\n\\nCompiler setup remains in:\\n- `tests/src/com.beachape/enumeratum-macros_3/1.9.0/build.gradle`\\n- Adds `-Yretain-trees`, required for supported `ValueEnumMacros.find*ValueEntriesImpl` use.\\n\\nConclusion: the remaining dynamic-access sites in `enumeratum.ValueEnumMacros$ValueOfFromExpr.unapply` should be left uncovered rather than covered via unsupported internal or Native-Image-unsafe mechanisms.\", \"textSignature\": \"{\\\"v\\\":1,\\\"id\\\":\\\"msg_0034f1349302b464016a3e6aab60bc8197a5595979e785a4cb\\\",\\\"phase\\\":\\\"final_answer\\\"}\"}], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"oca/gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 23899, \"output\": 2333, \"cacheRead\": 49664, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 75896, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"total\": 0}}, \"stopReason\": \"stop\", \"timestamp\": 1782475394076, \"responseId\": \"resp_0034f1349302b464016a3e6a82b30c8197b946473ab3b31160\"}}\n[recv] {\"type\": \"turn_end\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"thinking\", \"thinking\": \"**Exploring Scala configurations**\\n\\nI think I need to configure macro modules. I might configure